# Provenance Schema Contract

Every data-pack field in RHT-NAV carries provenance. The canonical TypeScript
shape is:

```ts
export type ProvenanceField<T> = {
  value: T;
  source: string;           // Human-readable: "CDC PLACES", "CMS POS", "HRSA AHRF"
  sourceUrl: string;        // Primary-source URL
  vintage: string;          // ISO date or year+quarter: "2025-Q4", "2023"
  retrievedOn: string;      // ISO8601 of the fetch
  methodology?: string;     // Optional short note, e.g. "5-year ACS estimate"
};
```

The canonical Python shape in `scripts/build_data_pack.py` and
`scripts/agents/` is a dataclass with identical field names.

## Rules

- A field without all five required properties is invalid and must not ship.
- If a value is not yet available, emit it as:
  ```ts
  { value: null, source, sourceUrl, vintage: null, retrievedOn: null }
  ```
  and render `<DataComingSoon source={source} field={name} />` client-side.
- `src/components/module-sources.tsx` renders the `source` + `sourceUrl` of
  every ProvenanceField displayed on the page. Do not bypass it.
- The `/data-methodology` page is generated from provenance metadata — do not
  hand-edit it.

## When adding a new data source

1. Add a row to the allow-list in `src/config/allowed-sources.ts` (create if
   missing) with `{ id, displayName, homepageUrl, citation }`.
2. Reference it by `id` from every ProvenanceField that uses it.
3. Add a scheduled refresher in `scripts/agents/` if the source updates on a
   cadence.
